 | A-020 | `GET /api/v1/document-files/{document_id}/download/` returns a 15-minute local download descriptor shaped as `/api/v1/local-document-files/{document_id}/download/?expires_at=...` rather than a true external signed URL, and all sensitivity levels use the same `documents.file.download` permission until the source documents define a concrete role/sensitivity matrix. | `api-contracts.md` §26.2 allows either signed URL response or native stream but does not define local-dev URL mechanics or expiry length. `auth-permissions.md` maps the endpoint to `documents.file.download` plus a sensitivity check, but the generic document-file foundation has no implementable object-level matrix yet. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §26.2; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` endpoint map; `docs/source/data-model.md` §16.1; `docs/slices/003D-secure-document-download-with-audit.md` | 003D-secure-document-download-with-audit | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-05 | Replace the local descriptor with real object-store signed URLs when a production storage adapter exists. Add sensitivity-specific object checks when the source matrix is defined; current tests assert the generic permission path and no metadata leakage. |
 | A-021 | Activating a draft loan-policy config retires any previously active loan-policy config and sets its `effective_to` to the day before the new config's `effective_from`. New configs must start as `draft`; activation is the only API path to `active`. | `api-contracts.md` §41.1 names an activate endpoint and `data-model.md` §25.1 defines `draft`/`active`/`retired`, but the source does not state exact overlap/retirement semantics. Retiring the prior active config preserves one current policy version without inventing calculation rules. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §41.1; `docs/source/data-model.md` §25.1 and §26.3; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M01-FR-001/M01-FR-002/M01-FR-015 | 003E-versioned-configuration-shell | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-05 | Future policy-governance slices should confirm whether overlapping active policies are ever allowed by loan product/member segment; if so, replace the global retirement rule with a source-backed product/segment scope. |
